Tyrosin kinase inhibitors (TKI), have dramatically changed the natural history 
of chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) leading to an impressive increase in overall 
survival rates and allowing many CML patients to achieve a close-to-normal life 
expectancy. Unfortunately, there is growing evidence that these drugs are not 
curative, about 30-35% of the patients who receive imatinib become resistant or 
