Artefacts and Family Resemblance.

Garbacz P(1).

Author information:
(1)Department of Philosophy, John Paul II Catholic University of Lublin, Lublin, 
Poland.

I develop in this paper a conception of artefacts based on L. Wittgenstein's 
idea of family resemblance. My approach peruses the notion of frame, which was 
invented in cognitive psychology as an operationisable extension of this 
philosophical idea. Following the metaphor of life-cycle I show how this 
schematic notion of frame may be filled with the content relevant for artefacts 
if we consider them from the point of view of their histories. The resulting 
conception of artefacts provides a new insight into the current debate on 
artefact categorisation.

